a:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Salesforce Flow is best suited for Salesforce admins, enterprises, sales operations, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Tallyfy, meanwhile, shines for small businesses, process documentation, client workflows, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 1999, Salesforce Flow describes itself as \"Salesforce's declarative automation engine for complex business processes.\" Tallyfy, established in 2015, positions itself as \"Process and workflow management for documenting and tracking business procedures.\" With 16 years between them, Salesforce Flow brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Tallyfy offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
b:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Salesforce Flow** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (7.0 vs 6.0), more features (10 vs 7). However, this does not mean Tallyfy is a poor choice — far from it. Tallyfy excels in its own right, particularly for small businesses and process documentation.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value extremely powerful for salesforce automation, go with Salesforce Flow. If simple process documentation matters more to you, Tallyfy is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
